trans-unit.source: Provides a user interface for selecting an XML file using a standard <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.OpenFileDialog"></xref> box.
<xref:System.Web.UI.Design.XmlFileEditor> is a <xref:System.Drawing.Design.UITypeEditor> that provides a dialog for selecting an XML file for a file name property.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Web.UI.Design.XmlFileEditor"></xref> class.
Edits the value of the specified object using the specified service provider and context.
A service provider is provided so that any required editing services can be obtained.
An <xref href="System.ComponentModel.ITypeDescriptorContext"></xref> that can be used to gain additional context information.
A service provider object through which editing services may be obtained.
An instance of the value being edited.
The new value of the object.
If the value of the object has not changed, this method should return the same object it was passed.
Gets the editing style associated with this editor, using the specified <xref href="System.ComponentModel.ITypeDescriptorContext"></xref> object.
An <xref href="System.ComponentModel.ITypeDescriptorContext"></xref> that can be used to gain additional context information.
A <xref href="System.Drawing.Design.UITypeEditorEditStyle"></xref> enumeration value indicating the provided editing style.
If the method is not supported in the specified context, this will return the <xref href="System.Drawing.Design.UITypeEditorEditStyle.None"></xref> identifier.
